ne of the Boys\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Katy Perry]]\n| cover      = Katy Perry - One of the Boys.png\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2008|06|17}}\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{flatlist|\n*[[Pop rock]]<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/sep/14/popandrock20 |first= Stephanie |last= Merritt |title= Pop review: Katy Perry, One of the Boys |work= [[The Guardian]] |date= September 14, 2008 |quote= Elsewhere, One of the Boys offers solid pop-rock, co-written with the likes of Cathy Dennis and influenced by Alanis, Avril and Liz Phair. |accessdate= August 21, 2014 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170710082545/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/sep/14/popandrock20 |archive-date= July 10, 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref>\n*[[soft rock]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/sep/19/popandrock2|title=Pop review, Katy Perry: One of the Boys|website=[[The Guardian]]|first=Dorian|last=Lynskey|date=September 18, 2008|accessdate=October 15, 2019|quote=Her producers furnish the punchy soft-rock...|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190421080202/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/sep/19/popandrock2|archive-date=April 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n| length     = 43:36\n| label      = [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n*Katy Perry\n*[[Greg Wells]]\n*[[Dr. Luke]]\n*[[Max Martin]]\n*[[Benny Blanco]]\n*[[Glen Ballard]]\n*[[David A. Stewart|Dave Stewart]]\n*[[Butch Walker]]\n*[[S*A*M and Sluggo]]\n*[[Ted Bruner]]\n}}\n| prev_title = [[Ur So Gay (EP)|Ur So Gay]]\n| prev_year  = 2007\n| next_title = The Hello Katy Australian Tour EP\n| next_year  = 2009\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n| artist     = Katy Perry studio album\n| prev_title = [[Katy Hudson (album)|Katy Hudson]]\n| prev_year  = 2001\n| title      = One of the Boys\n| year       = 2008\n| next_title = [[Teenage Dream (Katy Perry album)|Teenage Dream]]\n| next_year = 2010\n}}\n{{Singles\n | name        = One of the Boys\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[I Kissed a Girl]]\n | single1date = April 28, 2008\n | single2     = [[Hot n Cold]]\n | single2date = September 9, 2008\n | single3     = [[Thinking of You (Katy Perry song)|Thinking of You]]\n | single3date = January 12, 2009\n | single4     = [[Waking Up in Vegas]]\n | single4date = April 21, 2009\n}}\n}}\n'''''One of the Boys''''' is the second [[studio album]]<!--second is correct as Katy Hudson was her first album, and do NOT add any additional detail on chronology; the only important thing to note in opening sentence is that this is her second studio album--> by American singer [[Katy Perry]]. It was released on June 17, 2008 by [[Capitol Records]]. During its production, Perry was dropped from two record labels and went through two canceled albums. She collaborated with producers [[Greg Wells]], [[Dr. Luke]], [[David A. Stewart]], and [[Max Martin]], among others, on the album, and wrote all of its songs with assistance of other producers and writers. The [[Extended play|EP]] ''[[Ur So Gay (EP)|Ur So Gay]]'', containing the [[Ur So Gay|promotional single of the same name]], was released to generate interest in the singer and the album.\n\n''One of the Boys'' is Perry's first on a major label and first under the stage name Katy Perry, following her debut ''[[Katy Hudson (album)|Katy Hudson]]'', which was released under her real name on [[Pamplin Music|Red Hill Records]]. It received mixed reception from critics, with some deeming it as being filled with \"potential hits\" and others criticizing Perry's vocal performance. Commercially, it debuted at number nine on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], selling over 47,000 copies in its first week of sales, and also peaked within the top-ten charts in Austria, Canada, Denmark, Germany, Ireland, Mexico, Norway, and Switzerland. ''One of the Boys'' earned Perry two [[Grammy Award]] nominations, and has sold 7 million copies worldwide, being her 2nd highest-selling album to date. It has been certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]].\n\nThe album's lead single \"[[I Kissed a Girl]]\" became Perry's first [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] number-one single; the second single \"[[Hot n Cold]]\" reached number three in the United States, while topping the charts in Germany, Canada, the Netherlands, and Austria. The third single \"[[Thinking of You (Katy Perry song)|Thinking of You]]\" reached the top-thirty in the US, while the final single \"[[Waking Up in Vegas]]\" became a top-ten hit. To further promote the album, Perry embarked on three tours: the 2008 [[Warped Tour]], her first solo world tour, the [[Hello Katy Tour]], and served as an opening act in [[No Doubt]]'s [[2009 Summer Tour]].\n\n==Background==\nPerry's change in record label, and adoption of a pseudonymous surname accompanied a shift from the Christian rock of her debut album ''[[Katy Hudson (album)|Katy Hudson]]''.<ref>[http://www.crossrhythms.co.uk/articles/news/One_Of_The_Boys/30669/p1/ \"One of the Boys: Pop singer Katy Perry talks about her forthcoming album\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080615020058/http://www.crossrhythms.co.uk/articles/news/One_Of_The_Boys/30669/p1/ |date=June 15, 2008 }}. ''[[Cross Rhythms]]''. February 19, 2008. Retrieved 2012-11-20.</ref> The singer stated that she had been working on the album since she was eighteen years old. During the making of the album, Perry was dropped from two record labels and went through two canceled albums. During this time, Perry had written close to seventy songs.<ref name=Prefixmag.com>{{cite web |first=Mike |last=Burr |date=February 6, 2008 |url=http://www.prefixmag.com/features/katy-perry/interview/17027/ |title=Katy Perry: Interview |work=Prefix |accessdate=September 10, 2010 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66Fdt92X4?url=http://www.prefixmag.com/features/katy-perry/interview/17027/ |archive-date=March 18, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Perry collaborated with producers [[Greg Wells]], [[Dr. Luke]], [[David A. Stewart]], and [[Max Martin]] among others on the album.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/press_releases/katy_perry_to_release_debut_album_one_of_the_boys.html |title=Katy Perry to Release Debut Album 'One of the Boys' &#124; News @ |publisher=Ultimate-guitar.com |date=April 11, 2008 |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120116202802/http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/press_releases/katy_perry_to_release_debut_album_one_of_the_boys.html |archivedate=January 16, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Perry co-wrote every song on the album as well as writing three of the songs herself.\n\nOnce signed to Capitol, label head [[Jason Flom]] started work on a new album by convincing Dr. Luke to go back into the studio with Perry, with the two having already worked together on the abandoned Columbia sessions. Together with Max Martin they wrote and cut \"[[I Kissed a Girl]]\" and \"[[Hot n Cold]]\". Perry then collaborated again with Greg Wells, who she had also worked with on the Columbia album, creating the songs \"[[Ur So Gay]]\" and \"Mannequin\". According to Perry's A&R [[Chris Anokute]] they ended up with five new songs and then chose six of the songs from the shelved Columbia album to compile ''One of the Boys''.<ref name=hitquarters.com>{{cite web |url=http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/opar/intrview_Chris_Anokute_Interview.html |title=Interview with Chris Anokute |publisher=[[HitQuarters]] |date=October 18, 2010 |accessdate=October 25, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706033327/http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview%2Fopar%2Fintrview_Chris_Anokute_Interview.html |archive-date=July 6, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> When talking about the songs on the album Perry said that she released the single \"Ur So Gay\" as an introduction to the album:\n{{cquote|The album will have a lot of the same characteristics [as \"Ur So Gay\"], though. There will be lots of storytelling, because lyrics are important to me. There are a few songs that will make you cry, but there are others to make you dance and sing. Every song is on the album for a specific reason.<ref name=Prefixmag.com/>}}\n\n==Music and lyrics==\n===Themes and influences===\nAlthough Perry's musical style and way of [[musical composition|composing]] ironic and bawdy songs has been heavily compared to the style of singers [[Avril Lavigne]] and [[Lily Allen]],<ref>{{cite web |author=Climatempo |url=http://www.abril.com.br/noticia/diversao/no_345325.shtml |title=Katy Perry \u00e9 revela\u00e7\u00e3o do mesmo fil\u00e3o de Avril Lavigne e Lily Allen |publisher=Abril.com |date=September 30, 2008 |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |language=Portuguese |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927170433/http://www.abril.com.br/noticia/diversao/no_345325.shtml |archivedate=September 27, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> the singer was influenced by [[Queen (band)|Queen]] and [[Freddie Mercury]] in particular.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nme.com/news/queen/40017 |title=Freddie Mercury inspired Katy Perry to 'Kiss a Girl' &#124; News |publisher=Nme.com |date=September 26, 2008 |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106041511/http://www.nme.com/news/queen/40017 |archive-date=January 6, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> All songs on the album were written by Perry, assisted by musicians Greg Wells, [[Max Martin]], [[Dr. Luke]], Cathy Dennis, [[Desmond Child]], [[Andreas Carlsson]], [[Sam Hollander]], [[Dave Katz]], [[S*A*M and Sluggo]], [[Ted Bruner]], Scott Cutler, Anne Preven, [[David A. Stewart|Dave Stewart]], and [[Glen Ballard]]. The album includes several tracks that tell stories \u2014 a balance of sad songs and happier tunes. About these opposites, she said, \"I think people can appreciate a songwriter who shows different sides..... I've put everything into [this album] and I feel like it's my baby.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mvremix.com/urban_blogs/2008/04/15/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys-album-press-release/ |title=Katy Perry -One of the Boys- Album Press Release &#124; MVRemix Urban |publisher=Mvremix.com |date=July 15, 2008 |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120321234209/http://mvremix.com/urban_blogs/2008/04/15/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys-album-press-release/ |archive-date=March 21, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Songs===\n[[File:Life Ball 2009 Katy Perry 4.jpg|thumb|left|180px|Perry performing \"[[I Kissed a Girl]]\" at the [[Life Ball]] in May 2009 in Vienna, Austria]]\nThe opening track is the title track \"One of the Boys\", where Perry express that she does not want to \"be one of the boys of her love interest\", describing the song, Charles A. Hohman from ''[[PopMatters]]'' noted that \"she used to belch the alphabet and tape down her tits, but one summer, the tomboy lifestyle just didn't hold her interest, so she started 'studying [[Lolita]] religiously' and noticing guys noticing her.\"<ref name=\"PopMatters\">{{cite magazine|url= http://www.popmatters.com/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys/|magazine= PopMatters|title= One of the Boys|date= June 30, 2008|access-date= February 9, 2017|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170601040122/http://www.popmatters.com/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys/|archive-date= June 1, 2017|url-status= live}}</ref> The second track is the lead single \"[[I Kissed a Girl]]\" generated some controversy, dealing with the subject of [[lesbian]]ism. The song was inspired by actress [[Scarlett Johansson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://musica.terra.com.br/interna/0,,OI3126661-EI1267,00-Katy+Perry+diz+que+I+Kissed+a+Girl+e+inspirada+em+Scarlett+Johansson.html|title=Katy Perry diz que 'I Kissed a Girl' \u00e9 inspirada em Scarlett \u2013 Terra \u2013 M\u00fasica|publisher=Musica.terra.com.br|date=June 26, 2008|accessdate=December 11, 2011|language=Portuguese|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928105129/http://musica.terra.com.br/interna/0,,OI3126661-EI1267,00-Katy+Perry+diz+que+I+Kissed+a+Girl+e+inspirada+em+Scarlett+Johansson.html|archive-date=September 28, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref> Musically, it is a [[pop rock]] track.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2008/05/30/how-katy-perry-went-christian-rock-i-kissed-girl|title=How Katy Perry went from Christian rock to ''I Kissed a Girl''|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=February 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326053409/http://www.ew.com/article/2008/05/30/how-katy-perry-went-christian-rock-i-kissed-girl|archive-date=March 26, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/katy_perry/biography/|title=Katy Goes Pop|date=June 2008|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|accessdate=February 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090414125836/http://www.people.com/people/katy_perry/biography/|archive-date=April 14, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref> It contains influences of [[New wave music|new wave]]<ref name=rollingstone>{{cite web|last=Frehsee |first=Nicole |title=One of the Boys: Katy Perry: Music Review: Rolling Stone |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/reviews/album/21026892/review/21127345/one_of_the_boys |work=Rolling Stone |accessdate=January 31, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080617120000/http://www.rollingstone.com/reviews/album/21026892/review/21127345/one_of_the_boys|archivedate=June 17, 2008}}</ref> and runs through a throbbing beat<ref name=slant>{{cite web|last=Cinquemani|first=Sal|title=Katy Perry: One of the Boys|url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys/1397|work=Slant Magazine|access-date=February 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203053225/http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys/1397|archive-date=December 3, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> and an organic instrumental thump, according to [[About.com]]'s Bill Lamb.<ref name=about/> The track features instrumentation provided by drums, guitars and bass.<ref name=about>{{cite web|last=Lamb|first=Bill|title=Katy Perry \u2013 \"I Kissed a Girl\"|url=http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/ikissedagirl.htm|work=About.com|publisher=About.com|accessdate=February 9, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120130225849/http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/ikissedagirl.htm|archivedate=January 30, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The song sparked controversy for its [[homosexual]] themes. The album's third song is \"Waking Up In Vegas\",   the song has been described as a [[power pop]] and [[pop rock]] song.<ref name=\"Power\">{{cite web |url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/music/84245/SINGLE-Katy-Perry-Waking-Up-In-Vegas |title=SINGLE \u2013 Katy Perry: Waking Up In Vegas |first=Sarah-Louise |last=James |work=[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|Daily Star]] |publisher=[[Northern & Shell]] |date=June 10, 2009 |accessdate=March 27, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505075033/http://www.dailystar.co.uk/music/84245/SINGLE-Katy-Perry-Waking-Up-In-Vegas |archive-date=May 5, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> The song deals with trips with friends to [[Las Vegas]]. \"Thinking of You\" is the first [[ballad]] of the album. It is a [[downtempo]] [[pop rock]] song, as the singer reflects on settling for the second best: \"You said move on, where do I go?\"/\"I guess second best, it is all I will know\", she sings. Reviewing the song, editor ''CT'' from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' described it as \"a mid-'90s [[No Doubt]] pop/rock palette\".<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Katy Perry \u2013 Thinking of You|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jES_3Bf3jTYC&pg=PA40|access-date=February 9, 2017|date=January 10, 2009|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|author=CT|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170216212901/https://books.google.com/books?id=jES_3Bf3jTYC&pg=PA40|archive-date=February 16, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe fifth track is  \"Mannequin\". \"[[Ur So Gay]]\" was composed as a tool of revenge by the singer on her ex-boyfriend,<ref>{{cite web |author=Nekesa Mumbi Moody Da AP |url=http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Musica/0,,MUL351661-7085,00-CANTORA+FAZ+MUSICA+PARA+SE+VINGAR+DE+EXNAMORADO+GAY.html |title=G1 > M\u00fasica \u2013 NOT\u00cdCIAS \u2013 Cantora faz m\u00fasica para se vingar de ex-namorado 'gay' |publisher=G1.globo.com |date=March 15, 2008 |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |language=Portuguese |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815191923/http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Musica/0,,MUL351661-7085,00-CANTORA+FAZ+MUSICA+PARA+SE+VINGAR+DE+EXNAMORADO+GAY.html |archive-date=August 15, 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> where Perry satirizes his exaggerated [[emo|emo style]] and [[metrosexual]] attitude. It is a [[trip hop]] track with a moderate tempo.<ref name=\"arizona\">{{cite web |url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/azcentral/access/1702761281.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jun+21%2C+2008&author=Ed+Masley&pub=Arizona+Republic&desc=Perry+joins+the+forces+of+Warped&pqatl=google|title=Perry joins the forces of Warped|first=Ed |last=Masley|publisher=Arizona Central |date=June 21, 2008 |accessdate=July 1, 2012}}</ref>  In the seventh track \"[[Hot n Cold]]\", Perry discusses the theme of uncertainty and the ups and downs of relationships. It is a [[synthpop]] song which utilizes [[guitars]] and [[synthesizers]].<ref name=\"DigitalSpy\">{{cite web|url= http://www.digitalspy.com/music/single-reviews/review/a133632/katy-perry-hot-n-cold/|website= Digital Spy|title= Katy Perry \u2013 Hot n Cold (Review)|date= October 28, 2008|access-date= February 9, 2017|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20171201065420/http://www.digitalspy.com/music/single-reviews/review/a133632/katy-perry-hot-n-cold/|archive-date= December 1, 2017|url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=musicomh>{{cite web|url= http://www.chartattack.com/news/2008/07/08/katy-perry/|publisher= Chart Attack|title= Katy Perry \u2013 One of the Boys|date= July 8, 2008|access-date= February 9, 2017|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170608113428/http://www.chartattack.com/news/2008/07/08/katy-perry/|archive-date= June 8, 2017|url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"CA\">{{cite web |title= Katy Perry \u2014 One Of The Boys |date= July 8, 2008 |work= [[ChartAttack]] |url= http://www.chartattack.com/news/2008/07/08/katy-perry/ |accessdate= June 19, 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150620010857/http://www.chartattack.com/news/2008/07/08/katy-perry/ |archive-date= June 20, 2015 |url-status= live }}</ref> \"If You Can Afford Me\" cops a mixed message about female [[materialism]].<ref name=\"PopMatters\"/> Sal Cinquemani from ''[[Slant Magazine]]'' compared the song with [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]'s song \"[[Material Girl]]\" (1984).<ref name=\"Slant\">{{cite web|url= http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys|publisher= Slant|title= Katy Perry One Of The Boys|date= June 13, 2008|access-date= February 9, 2017|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150924150239/http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys|archive-date= September 24, 2015|url-status= live}}</ref> \"Lost\" and \"I'm Still Breathing\" are both [[ballad]]s, in the first, she sings: \"I leave the gas on/Walk the alleys in the dark\", the verse use a [[metaphor]] for a dying relationship.<ref name=\"Slant\"/>\n\n==Release and promotion==\n{{see also|Warped Tour 2008|2009 Summer Tour|Hello Katy Tour}}\nThe album was first released on June 17, 2008. It was released in separate editions: the standard edition, the Australian Tour edition,<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/B002FOFXEW \"Amazon.com: One of the Boys: Australian Tour Edition (Slip): Katy Perry: Music\"]. ''Amazon.com''. Retrieved December 29, 2010.</ref> which contains the standard [[CD]] plus a bonus CD (which was also released as a separate [[Extended play|EP]] on the Australian [[iTunes Store]])<ref name=\"itunes.apple.com\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/australian-tour-ep/id715997894|title=Australian Tour EP by Katy Perry on Apple Music|publisher=|access-date=March 28, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926064436/https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/australian-tour-ep/id715997894|archive-date=September 26, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> containing an acoustic version of \"[[Thinking of You (Katy Perry song)|Thinking of You]]\" and remixes, the special edition,<ref>[http://www.atomicmall.com/view.php?id=730911 \"KATY PERRY One of the Boys CD IN DIGIPAK - Music CDs\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707184052/http://www.atomicmall.com/view.php?id=730911 |date=July 7, 2011 }}. ''Atomic Mall''. Retrieved December 29, 2010.</ref> which is packaged in a [[digipak]] and contains four bonus tracks, and the Japanese [[re-issue]].<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/B002FRNCP6 \"Amazon.com: One of the Boys (Special Edition) (Incl. Bonus Tracks): Katy Perry: Music\"]. ''Amazon.com''. Retrieved December 29, 2010.</ref> The European, Japanese, and iTunes editions of the album all contain bonus tracks.\n[[File:Katy Perry YouTube.jpg|thumb|right|Perry performing the opening act for [[YouTube Live]] in 2008]]\nUpon its release, the singer has been heavily criticized for her song, \"[[Ur So Gay]]\", considered by the site [http://www.thenewgay.net/ The New Gay] to be [[homophobia|homophobic]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/ult90u438730.shtml |title=Folha Online - Ilustrada - Ex-gospel, cantora faz sucesso com beijo l\u00e9sbico - 28/08/2008 |publisher=www1.folha.uol.com.br |date=August 28, 2008 |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |language=Portuguese |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111224121120/http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/ult90u438730.shtml |archive-date=December 24, 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> The author of the publication added, \"It's time to Katy Perry to stop talking nonsense\" because \"the song trots out a number of tired gay stereotypes to condemn one of Perry's ex-boyfriends and includes a paradoxical chorus\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thenewgay.net/2008/06/katy-perry-new-gay-interview.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828211801/http://www.thenewgay.net/2008/06/katy-perry-new-gay-interview.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=August 28, 2008 |title=Katy Perry: The New Gay Interview |publisher=The New Gay |date=June 10, 2008 |accessdate=December 11, 2011 }}</ref> Jane Czyzselska from ''[[The Guardian]]'' commented that \"Perry's song is a rather sweet, refreshing antidote to the avalanche of overtly sexualized boy-grinds-girl songs.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/aug/08/gayrights.usa |location=London |work=The Guardian |title=A kiss is just a kiss |first=Jane |last=Czyzselska |date=August 8, 2008 |access-date=December 12, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924230844/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/aug/08/gayrights.usa |archive-date=September 24, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> She promoted the song in Portugal, and it was not very well received by the public. Her first single, \"[[I Kissed a Girl]]\", became a worldwide controversy. Despite the context, Perry mentioned several times that she does not define herself as [[heterosexual]] <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xjt75_8jjVE |title=Archived copy |access-date=March 13, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140617062712/http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xjt75_8jjVE |archive-date=June 17, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CBjN4DgDLCc |title=Archived copy |access-date=March 13, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190530193935/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CBjN4DgDLCc |archive-date=May 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qj9Ar0eX4AE</ref>. She has been strongly criticized by the [[homosexuality|LGBT]] community, who believe that the singer used music to make money and not on behalf of homosexuals, and by critics who claimed that music leads the girls to be lesbian.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://veja.abril.com.br/081008/p_186.shtml |title=Revista VEJA |date=October 8, 2008 |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |language=Portuguese |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111126161859/http://veja.abril.com.br/081008/p_186.shtml |archivedate=November 26, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> The song was criticized by the local headquarters of the evangelical Havens Corners Church, which has set the following sentence in its garden in September 2008: \"I kissed a girl and liked it. So I went to hell.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universomix.info/wp/religiao/evangelicos-associam-musica-de-katy-perry-ao-inferno/ |title=Evang\u00e9licos associam m\u00fasica de Katy Perry ao inferno \u00bb Universo Mix |publisher=Universomix.info |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |language=Portuguese |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091207064016/http://www.universomix.info/wp/religiao/evangelicos-associam-musica-de-katy-perry-ao-inferno/ |archivedate=December 7, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://dykerama.uol.com.br/src/?mI=5&cID=23&iID=1579 |title=:: Dykerama \u2013 Katy Perry criticada por m\u00fasica sobre beijo l\u00e9sbico :: |publisher=Dykerama.uol.com.br |date=August 18, 2008 |accessdate=December 11, 2011 |language=Portuguese |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110825060534/http://dykerama.uol.com.br/src/?mI=5&cID=23&iID=1579 |archivedate=August 25, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> To promote the album Perry embarked on three tours: the [[Warped Tour 2008]], her first solo world tour, the [[Hello Katy Tour]], with 89 shows performed, and [[No Doubt]]'s [[Summer Tour 2009 (No Doubt)|Summer Tour 2009]] as its opening act.\n\n==Singles==\nThe album's lead single, \"[[I Kissed a Girl]]\" was released in late April and subsequently soared up the charts. \"I Kissed a Girl\" was a commercial success. It topped the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 chart, becoming the 1000th chart-topper of the rock era. The song has since become a major worldwide hit, and along with the United States, it has topped the charts in more than twenty countries, including Australia, Canada, Ireland, and the United Kingdom. The second single, \"[[Hot n Cold]]\", made it onto the chart after the album came out due to digital downloads. It was released in early September, and peaked at number three on the US charts, making it Perry's second consecutive top five single.<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=katy perry|chart=Hot 100}} \"The Billboard Hot 100\"]. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''. January 14, 2009.</ref> On November 14, the song became Perry's first number one on radio airplay. It is officially one of the ten best-selling digitally downloaded songs of all time after its initial run.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart_watch/28975/week-ending-march-1-2009-theyre-not-exactly-burnin-up/ |title=Week Ending March 1, 2009: They're Not Exactly 'Burnin' Up' - Chart Watch |publisher=New.music.yahoo.com |date=March 4, 2009 |accessdate=December 28, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090310125028/http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart_watch/28975/week-ending-march-1-2009-theyre-not-exactly-burnin-up |archive-date=March 10, 2009 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n\"[[Thinking of You (Katy Perry song)|Thinking of You]]\", the penultimate single, was originally planned to be the first single from the album, but was scrapped for \"I Kissed a Girl\" due to its surge in popularity. \"Thinking of You\" received a video in late April 2008, but the video was removed from YouTube and replaced by a new video after the single was re-released as the third international single from the album. Perry shot the second video with director [[Melina Matsoukas]] in the first week of December 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.videostatic.com/vs/2008/12/shot-katy-perry.html |title=Music Video News: SHOT: Katy Perry \u2013 Melina, director |publisher=Video Static |date=December 3, 2008 |accessdate=December 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090426070650/http://www.videostatic.com/vs/2008/12/shot-katy-perry.html |archivedate=April 26, 2009 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> The video for the single was released on December 23, 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.katyperry.com/newz.aspx?c=GB&id=12180 |title=News |publisher=Katy Perry |accessdate=December 28, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090223092204/http://katyperry.com/newz.aspx?c=GB |archive-date=February 23, 2009 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> The track peaked at number twenty-nine on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 on the week of February 12, 2009 where it remained for the next two weeks before declining to number thirty-one in its seventh week on the chart. \"[[Waking Up in Vegas]]\" is the fourth and final single from the album. It went for radio adds on April 21, 2009 in the US.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=16691 |title=Radio Industry News, Music Industry Updates, Arbitron Ratings, Music News and more! |magazine=FMQB |accessdate=December 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207200650/http://fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=16691 |archivedate=February 7, 2017 }}</ref> It was released to Australian radio on March 23, 2009, where it became the fourth most added song in its release week.<ref>[http://www.themusicnetwork.com.au/index.php?id=20 The Music Network] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090220220102/http://www.themusicnetwork.com.au/index.php?id=20 |date=February 20, 2009 }}</ref> Perry performed it on ''[[American Idol]]'' in May, resulting in a surge of sales for the song. The music video was shot by [[Joseph Kahn]] during March 2009 in Las Vegas and officially premiered on the [[iTunes Store]] in the US, and Australia on April 28, 2009. It peaked at number nine on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, becoming the third top-ten single from the album.\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| title =\n| subtitle =\n| state =\n<!-- Aggregate scores -->\n|MC = 47/100<ref name=\"mc_review\">{{cite web |title=One of the Boys reviews |url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/one-of-the-boys/katy-perry |website=Metacritic |accessdate=October 19, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100415010259/http://www.metacritic.com/music/artists/perrykaty/oneoftheboys |archive-date=April 15, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n<!-- Reviewers -->\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref name=AllMusic1/>\n| rev2 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev2Score = D-<ref>{{cite news |last=Koski |first=Genevieve |url=http://www.avclub.com/articles/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys,6983/ |title=Katy Perry: One of the Boys |newspaper=The A.V. Club |date=July 7, 2008 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100117135345/http://www.avclub.com/articles/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys,6983/ |archive-date=January 17, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Blender (magazine)|Blender]]''\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blender.com/guide/new/55161/one-boys.html |title=One of the Boys |publisher=Blender |date=June 17, 2008 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100109085825/http://www.blender.com/guide/new/55161/one-boys.html |archivedate=January 9, 2010 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev4Score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{cite news |author=Lynskey, Dorian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/sep/19/popandrock2 |title=CD: Katy Perry, One of the Boys &#124; Music |newspaper=The Guardian |date=September 19, 2008 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419192448/http://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/sep/19/popandrock2 |archive-date=April 19, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[Now (newspaper)|NOW]]''\n| rev5score = {{rating|2|5}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nowtoronto.com/music/album-reviews/katy-perry-2008-07-03/ |title=KATY PERRY: One Of The Boys (Capitol) |date=3 July 2008 |accessdate=11 February 2018 |work=[[NOW (newspaper)|NOW]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180212005514/https://nowtoronto.com/music/album-reviews/katy-perry-2008-07-03/ |archive-date=February 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev6Score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/reviews/album/21026892/review/21127345/one_of_the_boys?source=album_reviews_rssfeed |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080617120000/http://www.rollingstone.com/reviews/album/21026892/review/21127345/one_of_the_boys?source=album_reviews_rssfeed |archivedate=June 17, 2008 |accessdate=July 1, 2010 |title=One of the Boys \u2013 Katy Perry \u2013 Review |author=Frehsee, Nicole |date=June 26, 2008 |magazine=Rolling Stone}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[PopMatters]]''\n| rev7Score = {{rating|4|10}}<ref name=pop>{{cite web |last=Hohman |first=Charles A. |url=http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/60355/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys/ |title=Katy Perry: One of the Boys < PopMatters |publisher=Popmatters.com |date=July 1, 2008 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081010150724/http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/60355/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys/ |archive-date=October 10, 2008 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Slant Magazine]]''\n| rev8Score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys/1397 |title=Katy Perry: One of the Boys |magazine=Slant Magazine |date=June 15, 2008 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100611145325/http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys/1397 |archive-date=June 11, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]''\n| rev9Score = 3/10<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.spin.com/reviews/katy-perry-one-boys-capitol |title=Katy Perry, 'One of the Boys' (Capitol) |publisher=Spin.com |date=June 25, 2008 |accessdate=April 18, 2010 |author=Anderson, Stacey |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090302092555/http://www.spin.com/reviews/katy-perry-one-boys-capitol |archive-date=March 2, 2009 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]''\n| rev10score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite journal |title=Katy Perry: One of the Boys |date=October 2008 |work= [[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]] |page=105 }}</ref>\n}}\nThe album received generally mixed reviews from critics. On [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[Standard score|normalized]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album has received a score of 47, citing \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref name=\"meta\">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/artists/perrykaty/oneoftheboys |title=Katy Perry:One of the Boys (2008): Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=CNET Networks, Inc |accessdate=March 25, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090227060410/http://www.metacritic.com/music/artists/perrykaty/oneoftheboys |archive-date=February 27, 2009 |url-status=live }}</ref> A highly positive review came from Kerri Mason of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', who felt it was \"packed with potential hits.\"<ref name=\"billboard.com\">{{cite magazine |url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/reviews-album/one-of-the-boys-1003816207.story |title=One of the Boys |magazine=Billboard.com |date=September 14, 2009 |accessdate=December 28, 2009 |author=Mason, Kerri |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090426022632/http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/reviews-album/one-of-the-boys-1003816207.story |archivedate=April 26, 2009}}</ref> ''[[Blender (magazine)|Blender]]'' argued, \"Perry's creative-writing-class punch lines don't always justify her self-congratulatory drag-queen tone. But she hiccups quirkily enough, and myriad big-name producers (from [[Dr. Luke]] to [[Glen Ballard]]) keep the new-wave synth hooks hopping.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blender.com/guide/reviews.aspx?id=5184 |title=Katy Perry:One of the Boys Review on Blender |work=[[Blender (magazine)|Blender]] |accessdate=March 25, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090324043820/http://www.blender.com/guide/reviews.aspx?id=5184 |archive-date=March 24, 2009 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] of [[AllMusic]] gave the album two out of five stars, remarking it \"sinks to crass, craven depths that turn ''One of the Boys'' into a grotesque emblem of all the wretched excesses of this decade.\"<ref name=\"AllMusic1\">{{cite web |url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=one-of-the-boys-mw0000787236|pure_url=yes}} |title=AllMusic ((( One of the Boys > Overview ))) |accessdate=November 15, 2012 |author=Erlewine, Stephen Thomas |authorlink=Stephen Thomas Erlewine |work=[[AllMusic]]}}</ref> ''[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]'' wrote, \"[[Gwen Stefani]] should be nervous\", while Sal Cinquemani of [[Slant Magazine]] criticized Perry's vocal performances, and compared the title track to \"[[No Doubt]]'s '[[Just a Girl]]' sans personality and conviction\".<ref name=meta/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys |title=Katy Perry:One of the Boys Review on Slant Magazine |work=[[Slant Magazine]] |accessdate=March 25, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924150239/http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys |archive-date=September 24, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> Alex Miller of ''[[NME]]'' discouraged music consumers with \"even a passing interest in actually enjoying a record\" from buying it.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/9900 |title=Katy Perry:One of the Boys Review on NME |work=[[NME]] |accessdate=March 25, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116104108/http://www.nme.com/reviews/9900 |archive-date=January 16, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[Robert Christgau]] gave the album a [[Christgau's Consumer Guide: Albums of the '90s#Grading key|two-star honorable mention]] in his [[Robert Christgau#Consumer Guide|Consumer Guide]] review, citing \"I Kissed a Girl\" and \"One of the Boys\" as highlights while writing, \"She stopped taping her 'suckers' down, and kissing her girlfriend was just an experiment, but trumpeting her vulnerability she's as loud and laddish as a hockey fan\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|date=n.d.|url=https://www.robertchristgau.com/get_artist.php?id=6011&name=Katy+Perry|title=CG: Katy Perry|website=robertchristgau.com|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Year-end lists===\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n! Publication\n! Accolade\n! Rank\n! class=\"unsortable\"|{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]''\n| The 50 Best Pop Album Covers of the Past Five Years\n| {{center|16}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.complex.com/style/2013/11/best-pop-album-covers/katy-perry-teenage-dream |title=Archived copy |access-date=December 20, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181220230618/https://www.complex.com/style/2013/11/best-pop-album-covers/katy-perry-teenage-dream |archive-date=December 20, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''One of the Boys'' debuted at number nine on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], with 47,000 copies sold in the first-week released.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/956562/katy-perry-doubles-up-no-1s-on-billboard-200-digital-songs-charts |title=Katy Perry Doubles Up No. 1s on Billboard 200, Digital Songs Charts |last=Caulfield |first=Keith |date=August 1, 2010 |work=Billboard |publisher=Nielsen Business Media |accessdate=October 2, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100831145303/http://www.billboard.com/ |archive-date=August 31, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> The album has sold 1,710,000 copies in the United States as of February 2017 and has been certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA).<ref name=\"USsales\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7694308/ask-billboard-katy-perrys-career-song-album-sales|title=Ask Billboard: Katy Perry's Career Song & Album Sales|last=Trust|first=Gary|work=Billboard|date=February 20, 2017|accessdate=February 20, 2017|journal=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222052835/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7694308/ask-billboard-katy-perrys-career-song-album-sales|archive-date=February 22, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"riaa\"/> The album has been on the chart for ninety- two weeks. In Canada, the album debuted at number ten, and peaked at number six, It has since been certified double platinum by [[Music Canada]].<ref name=\"CRIA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cria.ca/goldplat.php |title=CRIA Gold & Platinum Certification |publisher=Canadian Recording Industry Association |accessdate=April 21, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100823041748/http://www.cria.ca/goldplat.php |archivedate=August 23, 2010 }}</ref>\n\nIn the United Kingdom, the album peaked at number eleven on the [[UK Albums Chart]], and has sold 718,000 copies as of April 2020.<ref name=\"uksales2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/artists-who-beat-the-second-album-slump__19500/|title=Artists who beat the second album slump|last=Myers|first=Justin|date=April 13, 2020|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref> It has since been certified 2\u00d7 Platinum by the [[British Phonographic Industry]].<ref name=\"bpi\"/> In Australia, it debuted at number eleven, and has been certified platinum by the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA), denoting over 70,000 copies sold.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aria.com.au/pages/httpwww.aria.com.aupageshttpwww.aria.com.aupagesARIACharts-Accreditations-2008Albums.htm |title=ARIA Charts - Accreditations - 2008 Albums |publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]] |accessdate=March 2, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410212857/http://www.aria.com.au/pages/httpwww.aria.com.aupageshttpwww.aria.com.aupagesARIACharts-Accreditations-2008Albums.htm |archive-date=April 10, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> In New Zealand, the album debuted and peaked at number seventeen. It has since been certified Gold, shipping over 7,500 copies.<ref name=\"radioscope.net.nz\">{{cite web|url=http://www.radioscope.net.nz/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=79&Itemid=61 |title=Latest Gold / Platinum Albums \u2013 RadioScope New Zealand |publisher=Radioscope.net.nz |accessdate=December 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110831040527/http://www.radioscope.net.nz/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=77&Itemid=61 |archivedate=August 31, 2011 }}</ref> ''One of the Boys'' has sold 7 million copies worldwide as of August 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1646527/katy-perry-fantasia-look-to-unseat-eminem-on-charts/|title=Katy Perry, Fantasia look to unseat Eminem on charts|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=August 26, 2010|publisher=[[MTV News]]|accessdate=February 28, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330100108/http://www.mtv.com/news/1646527/katy-perry-fantasia-look-to-unseat-eminem-on-charts/|archive-date=March 30, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column    = Producer(s)\n| title1          = One of the Boys\n| writer1         = [[Katy Perry]]\n| extra1          = [[Butch Walker]]\n| length1         = 4:07\n| title2          = [[I Kissed a Girl]]\n| writer2       